messages.messageBody:
6/4/03 17:27:

> << My parents used to live on Cudjoe,. . . . Cool place :) >>
>
>
> Oooooh, creepy name.
>
> For someone from far away who never heard of it, it sounds like a place where
> snarling, barking, unnaturally big and hairy vines grow that attack at night.

When my husband did his counselling intership, he was called out one night
to place a child who refused to go home because of some major problem.
Anway, the police called Alan in to take the report and deliver her to the
foster home.

The place was at 666 Bloody Gulch Road. Alan said he about fell over when
he read the name, and the poor girl looked terrified when they turned onto
the road. His supervisor told him later that they were really a great
foster family, though.

brenda
